  "text": "As the hardware performance of mobile devices rose to a level sufficient to execute high-performance web browsing engines (e.g., WebKit), many commodity mobile devices chose to employ native web browsers. The native browser handles every step of processing a web page request by itself in order to provide an interactive and dynamic browsing experience similar to that on a PC. Their interface, including zoom, feels more natural and their page loading time feels faster than their thin-client counterparts because they draw intermediate renderings during page loading and update the page being loaded continually [CITATION_1] .",
